## Ingredients

- [ ] 6 large egg yolks
- [ ] 2 cups (8 ounces) confectioners' sugar
- [ ] 1 cup light rum
- [ ] 1 quart heavy cream or half-and-half
- [ ] 1 cup cognac or Asbach brandy
- [ ] 1/2 cup orange liqueur, such as Grand Marnier or Cointreau
- [ ] Freshly grated nutmeg, for garnish

## Recipe

1. In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks with a whisk until light in color. Gradually whisk in the confectionersâ€™ sugar and then the rum
1. Refrigerate, uncovered, for 1 hour to dispel the eggy taste
1. Whisking constantly, add the heavy cream or half-and-half, cognac and orange liqueur
1. Refrigerate, covered, for at least 3 hours
1. Serve, garnishing each cup with freshly grated nutmeg

